<font color="#FF0000">HOLD ON MICHAEL!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov  8 22:32:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Thanks Anne!<br><br>
Michael:<br><br>
Hang Tough Brother!  The noise we hear is you lying outside the perimeter..in pain.  The noise you are soon to hear is this motley crew crawling through the wire to fetch you.  Back in the bunker..we've got hot Spam ..Koolaid..peaches and pound cake (If you say you like Ham and Lima Beans better..we will throw you back over the wire.)<br><br>
After we love the shit out of you..maybe it won't be so hard to love yourself.  If you don't love yourself...you can't love a Lady!  If you go around kicking your own ass..you end up hurting those who are trying to love you...end result you hurt them and yourself.<br><br>
We have jarheads, cannon cockers, grunts, medics, tunnel rats, pipe jockies, door gunners, search and rescue and helicopter pilots.  Collectively, we have an IQ of 150..that's 8 points (one per man..minus one point for the Marine..which equals 7) and 143 points for the helicopter pilot!<br><br>
Don't know what you did in Nam..but whatever it was we desperately need one more in our group!<br><br>
I don't want to appear too &quot;light&quot; while you are splattered all over the rice paddie.  Just want to say that I love you and want you to come aboard and share our good times and sad times.  We have gained strength from each other.  We'll give you some of ours... later, you can give us some of yours.<br><br>
Captain Edward Ramon, RVN 1966-67-69<br><br>
P.S.  Feel free to e-mail this old Comanche rotorhead.
